comments.body:
It sounds like ignoring sigpipe unconditionally (i.e., in Arrow C++ or AWS SDK C++ code) is generally considered a bad idea; however, ignoring it within the session where you're running into this problem is probably fine. I can't reproduce this locally but you could try something like this as a workaround:

{code:R}
cpp11::cpp_source(code = '
#include <csignal>
#include <cpp11.hpp>

[[cpp11::register]] void ignore_sigpipes() {
  signal(SIGPIPE, SIG_IGN);
}
')

ignore_sigpipes()
{code}
